## 📋 Engineering Blueprint: Off-Grid Modular Vortex Chiller
This summary serves as your permanent design record. It details the complete physics, fluid dynamics, and thermodynamic architectures established for your human-powered, solar-assisted micro-zone personal cooling and dehumidification system.
------------------------------
## I. The Core Concepts & Math

* The Mission: Deliver a precise 1-foot diameter stream of dry, deeply chilled air at 5 mph for a continuous 2-hour workout session inside a high-humidity environment.
* The Air Volume: Over 2 hours, the system moves 41,469 cubic feet of air (weighing 3,110 lbs).
* The Thermal Load: Dropping this air volume from 80°F (70% RH) to 50°F requires removing 22,392 BTUs of sensible heat and condensing 13.7 lbs (1.6 gallons) of water vapor (13,700 BTUs of latent heat), totaling 36,092 BTUs of required cooling energy.
* The Approach: A direct human-powered compressor fails due to energy deficits (humans max out at ~500 Wh over 2 hours). This system solves that by treating a localized fluid loop as a "Thermal Battery"—harvesting solar power slowly all day to discharge a massive burst of cold energy during the workout.

------------------------------
## II. Air Stream & Cooling Architecture (The Vortex Tunnel)

* Housing: A horizontal, inline modular tunnel constructed from non-porous, waterproof High-Density Polyethylene (HDPE), externally insulated to prevent ambient condensation.
* The Modules: 12-inch diameter, 3-inch long monolithic aluminum cylinder blocks cored out to match the duct diameter.
* Interior Geometry: 5 to 7 fixed, internal 3D helical stators (vanes) milled directly into the core at a 45-degree twist pitch (36-inch rotation lead). This forces the air into a spinning vortex, throwing water droplets outward via centrifugal force while maintaining exceptionally low backpressure for the rowing machine fan.
* Weight Reduction: The exterior faces of the aluminum blocks are deeply pocketed to reduce raw thermal mass, allowing the system to flash-chill within 60 seconds of fluid activation.
* Connections: Machined ridges on the block edges utilize standard automotive V-band clamps with Viton O-rings for rapid, airtight modular stacking.
* Thermal Breaks: The heavy modules are supported by structural mounts made of G-10 Garolite or Delrin plastic to prevent structural sweating or cold loss to the frame.

------------------------------
## III. Fluid Dynamics & Micro-Drainage

* The Cooling Loop: 1/4" Internal Diameter (ID) soft copper tubing is wrapped tightly around exterior double-helix grooves milled into each aluminum block, secured with a highly conductive, moisture-proof thermal epoxy.
* The Fluid: A 35% ethanol/water mix (or commercial organic salt brine like Potassium Formate). This maintains an ultra-low viscosity at 20°F, eliminating the heavy pumping friction (head loss) caused by standard glycol.
* Main Transit Lines: Flexible 1/2" PEX lines completely isolated from each other. The supply line is centered inside an outer pipe filled with closed-cell polyurethane foam, achieving an uncompromised R-11 insulation rating.
* The Counter-Flow Path: Fluid lines daisy-chain between blocks so freezing liquid enters the module closest to the user (Deep-Chilling Zone) and exits through the block closest to the fan intake (Dehumidification Zone).
* The Capillary Drain: Microscopic weep holes are drilled at the 6 o'clock position of the blocks, feeding into an external sealed drainage box packed with a hydrophilic capillary matrix. When wet, the fabric forms a solid liquid seal, letting gravity pull water out without letting positive air pressure whistle through the drains.

------------------------------
## IV. The Staged Solar Thermal Battery

* Tank Layout: Five separate 55-gallon industrial drums (totaling 275 gallons of liquid) linked in series to create a progressive temperature gradient.
* Insulation: The entire barrel array is packed into a specialized vault boasting an extraordinary insulation rating of R-60 or better.
* Displacement Flow: A 12V DC brushless, automotive-grade coolant pump draws the absolute coldest liquid from the bottom of Drum 5. Warmed return fluid is gently diffused back into the top of Drum 1 via a low-velocity spray bar to maximize thermal stratification.
* Staged Chillers: Small, independent, highly efficient 12V/24V DC compressors sit between the drums, cooling the fluid in steps. This lowers the electrical footprint and allows the solar array to maximize its output even on low-sunlight or cloudy days.
* Bridge Circulation: A tiny secondary bridge pump routes fluid exclusively within the coldest barrels during off-workout hours to lock in peak thermal storage.
* Vapor Management: The drum heads are completely airtight to contain alcohol vapors, linked together by a 1/4" vacuum line that vents safely outside through a one-way pressure-relief breathing valve.

